headline: 3 US Dividend Stocks To Consider With At Least 3% Yield
summary: As U.S. markets face turbulence with major indexes experiencing consecutive weekly declines amid rising Treasury yields, investors are increasingly looking for stability in dividend stocks. In such an environment, stocks offering a yield of at least 3% can provide a reliable income stream while potentially mitigating some of the volatility seen in growth-oriented sectors.
